# Czech translations for tray4hermes UI strings.
# (Czech isn't actually a translation here — Czech IS the source
# language used during development, so the .mo file simply echoes
# the source. The compiled Czech translation is intentionally
# byte-identical to the source strings because every msgstr is
# already in Czech. But shipping a .mo for Czech means the
# runtime can still pick a Czech translation, validate the
# extraction pipeline, and honour ``--language cs`` even when the
# locale is something else. It also makes the build reproducible
# for future translators who want to fork off cs.po into de.po /
# sk.po / etc.)
